The paper introduces a new data visualization and exploration method that utilizes algorithms commonly used in machine learning and data analysis, such as locality sensitive hashing and Kruskal's minimum-spanning-tree algorithm. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper exemplifies the method in the area of cheminformatics, which involves analyzing and visualizing large amounts of chemical data, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
